headline: US greenhouse gas emissions rise before Trump policies even kick in
description: CO₂ emissions from the world's second-largest polluter have started rising again due to a cold winter and the use of coal to power data centers. The consequences of Donald Trump's attacks on climate action are expected to soon make the situation even worse.

Trump isolated after trade escalation with Europe over Greenland
description: The president's threats could undermine the agreement reached by the United States and the European Union in the summer of 2025.

headline: The Kurdish dream of autonomy in Syria ends
description: Under pressure from advancing government forces, the head of the Syrian Democratic Forces (SDF), Mazloum Abdi, signed an agreement with Syrian President Ahmed al-Sharaa formalizing the restoration of Damascus's authority over northeastern Syria.

headline: Valentino Garavani, fashion designer who founded Valentino, dies at 93
description: Renowned for the elegance of his designs, Garavani made vibrant red his signature color. The dress he created for Jackie Kennedy for her wedding to Aristotle Onassis brought him international fame. He died on January 19 at the age of 93.

headline: Jean Pisani-Ferry, economist: 'Is AI fueling a new wave of growth or a bubble?'
description: When two Nobel laureates disagree over the potential impact of artificial intelligence, it signals that the massive investments now underway carry risk, notes economist Jean Pisani-Ferry. Through its own savings, Europe is also exposed to those risks.

The strange airborne rescue of Gaza's donkeys, from Israel to Europe
description: Since 2022, Sharon Cohen, who runs an animal rescue group near Tel Aviv, has removed donkeys from Palestinian owners she accuses of mistreatment and sent them to shelters across Europe. The initiative has drawn outrage amid Gaza's deepening humanitarian crisis.

headline: Istanbul's ultra-violent gangs tighten their grip on the city
description: In Turkey's major cities, criminal gangs made up of teenagers and young adults have grown rapidly in recent years, fueled by a boom in synthetic drug trafficking.

headline: From Monroe to Trump: Two centuries of US interference in Latin America
description: From the Monroe Doctrine of 1823 to the intervention in Venezuela, Washington has dominated the American continent by force and through economic power. Faced with China's growing influence, Donald Trump has rejuvenated the notion of a 'manifest destiny.'
